Subject: [PATCH 1/3] =?UTF-8?q?mesh=20hooks:=20initial=20implementation=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20three=20hooks=20wired=20into=20server?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

New files:
- server-mesh-hook.h: mesh_hook_ctx, mesh_signal_window, mesh_compute_entropy

Modified:
- common.h: add mesh_port to common_params
- arg.cpp: add --mesh-port CLI flag
- server-task.h: add mesh_hooks, mesh_port to task_params
- server-task.cpp: parse mesh_hooks/mesh_port from request JSON
- server-context.cpp: wire in all three hooks + signal computation + async poll

Hook 1 (pre_inference): in launch_slot_with_task, fires on capability
  mismatch or context pressure
Hook 2 (post_prefill): at DONE_PROMPT→GENERATING, fires when first-token
  entropy exceeds threshold
Hook 3 (pre_response): in send_final_response, fires on max_tokens,
  very short response, high uncertainty, or tail entropy spike

Generation loop: per-token signal update + async poll every 16 tokens.

Token injection is stubbed (TODO comments) — hooks fire and log but
don't modify the prompt/KV cache yet.
