From 28dcebc281f65480889f98326013504dd87749f2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Michael Neale <michael.neale@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 15:35:44 +1000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] mesh hooks: implement token injection for Hook 1 and Hook
 3
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Hook 1 (pre_inference): when action=inject, tokenize the text and
append to task.tokens before slot processing. The model sees the
injected context as part of its prompt.

Hook 3 (pre_response): when action=inject, append text directly
to slot.generated_text before the response is sent to the client.

Async poll: append result text to generated_text when ready.

Tested end-to-end:
- Hook 1 inject: system note → model follows injected instruction
- Hook 3 inject: truncation note appended to response
- All three hooks fire in correct sequence
